body:
Even where malaria is eliminated or close to elimination, diagnostic capabilities, including quality assurance, should be maintained, and parasitological confirmation by microscopy (or by RDT) is recommended before treatment is administered. Where both malaria species coexist, bivalent RDTs should be used in order to differentiate P. falciparum from P. vivax. If microscopy is used, WHO standards for malaria microscopy training, certification and quality assurance should be in place.

The treatment of P. falciparum and P. vivax infections, however, differs (Table A2).
